Azure Policy can enforce: Storage must have classification tags

Sensitive data storage must: Use private endpoint, Disable public access, Enable encryption with CMK, Block replication to unapproved regions, Different controls per sensitivity level

Microsoft Purview – where configuration is done (Manual, Required)
Purview classification & labeling is configured only in Purview portal
Steps:

Open Microsoft Purview
Register data sources (Storage, SQL, etc.)
Run scans
Enable:

Sensitive info types (PII / PHI / PCI)
Classification rules
Sensitivity labels


Configure auto‑labeling policies
Review findings
(Optional) Export metadata to tags via automation

